works.description: I am doing this backwards. My company is the one infringing on another companies trademark. We have been informed by the other company to change it immediately. It has been changed by the webmasters of the site that they are on but when I run a google search for "CalPak Graphite" it is everywhere. We have a deadline to have this text removed before more action is taken agaist  us. So the problem is this; We have a product named "Graphite" It appears that another bag and luggage company trademarked that name several years ago. It was an accident and we have since changed the name to Rambler. If you run a google search for Graphite it comes up only on the Google search page. If you click the link when the new page opens it will say "Rambler" Can you please help me with this. Time is of the essence.
